<h2><br/>
Can life exist outside of the habitable zone?</h2>
<p><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-ie1GhSjpQX64p-Jkf3Er8A8oVRJof5gzFvQRRlRtOk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9jeGRpZy5maWxlcy53b3JkcHJlc3MuY29tLzIwMjMvMDcvMTQ1NmNkYmQtZjQzOS00OTc2LWFiM2MtZTkwOWIyOGE3YTRmLTEuanBnP3c9MTEwOA==" loading="lazy"/></p>
<p>Philip C. Ball</p>
<p>Speculation about conditions on Venus raises questions about our existing definitions</p>
<p>Read the full article at: <a href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/opinion/can-life-exist-outside-of-the-habitable-zone/4017685.article" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">www.chemistryworld.com</a></p>
